BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"AI & The Future of Education" Featuring Jeremy Gilbert\, Sara Soo
 d\, Moderated by Karen Smilowitz
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T183000Z
UID:2d5e826b0aae223aa6e62dc620b230e0@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an in-person Distinguished Panel event featurin Je
 remy Gilbert and Sara Sood\, moderated by Karen Smilowitz. \nTitle: "AI &
  The Future of Education"\nHigher education is at an inflection point. As 
 artificial intelligence rapidly reshapes how we teach\, learn\, and conduc
 t research\, universities face pressing questions about what this means fo
 r students\, faculty\, and institutions alike.\nThis panel brings together
  thought leaders from Northwestern to explore how AI is transforming the h
 igher education landscape — from the classroom to the research lab. Pane
 lists will discuss the opportunities and challenges AI presents for learni
 ng outcomes\, academic integrity\, institutional governance\, and the evol
 ving roles of educators and students. The conversation will also consider 
 how universities can thoughtfully adapt to ensure AI serves as a tool for 
 equity and excellence rather than a source of new inequities.\nLunch will 
 be provided. Registration is required.
LOCATION:Norris University Center\, 1999 Campus Drive\, Evanston\, IL
