BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:ISITA | The Chronicles of Two West African Kingdoms - Zachary Wrig
 ht\, Ali Diakite\, Mauro Nobili
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T181500Z
UID:542ed74309c77c6d373cd3dc3c1596e8@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Join the Institute for the Study of Islamic Thought in Africa 
 (ISITA) for a talk in our Islam in Africa - New Books in the Field series.
  \nLunch will be served at the talk.\nCo-sponsored by the Department of H
 istory.\nMauro Nobili\, Zachary Wright\, and Ali Diakite will discuss thei
 r new book\, The Chronicles of Two West African Kingdoms: TheTārīkh Ibn 
 Al-Mukhtār of the Songhay Empire and the Tārīkh Al-Fattāsh of the Cali
 phate of Ḥamdallāhi (The British Academy / Liverpool University Press\,
  2025).\nDescription: The Chronicles of Two West African Kingdoms present
 s a new reading of West African history from the fifteenth to the nineteen
 th centuries. Based on close analysis of Arabic manuscripts from Timbuktu 
 and other regions\, this volume provides key historical context from the S
 onghay Empire through the Caliphate of Ḥamdallāhi\, along with translat
 ions and Arabic editions of the long-obscured Tārīkh Ibn al-Mukhtār in 
 parallel with the later production known as the Tārīkh al-fattāsh. The 
 central observation that emerges from these texts is that Muslim scholars 
 in premodern West Africa\, who saw themselves as constitutive to the power
 ful kingdoms in the Western Sudan\, claimed almost unprecedented authority
  to shape reality through narration.\nDr. Mauro Nobili is Professor of His
 tory at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign.\nDr. Ali Diakite i
 s Cataloger for West African Manuscripts at the Hill Museum and Manuscript
  Library (Collegeville\, MN).\nDr. Zachary Wright is ISITA's Director\, as
  well as Professor in Residence and Associate Dean for Faculty Affairs at 
 Northwestern University in Qatar.
LOCATION:Harris Hall\, 1881 Sheridan Road\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/638332
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
